Since the [2.8 release|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/STASH-2796] it is possible to move a repo to a new project.

[The REST API to update a repo name|https://developer.atlassian.com/static/rest/stash/2.12.1/stash-rest.html#idp1561056] (PUT operation) doesn't include an example of how to do this.

You should use the payload below:

{code}
{
    "name":"New Name",
    "forkable":true|false,
    "public":true|false,
    "project":{
        "key":"NEWKEY"
    }
}
{code}

This documentation should be updated.

- clear the cookies
- go to https://stash.example.com/account;
- Stash redirects to the login page;
- upon successful login, the user is redirected to the project list.

There are bashisms in the setenv.sh. On Ubuntu system startup.sh complains with 
{noformat}
git@hybe:~$ current/bin/startup.sh
/srv/git/current/bin/setenv.sh: 106: [[: not found
{noformat}

Ubuntu and other Linux flavours are not using {{bash}} as system shell (aka /bin/sh). See https://wiki.ubuntu.com/DashAsBinSh#A.5B.5B for differences
